+/*
+ * RMBlast custom nucleotide substitution matrices. -RMH-
+ *
+ * These matrices are used by RMBlastN for repeat masking searches.
+ * The KA parameter values (lambda, K, H, alpha, beta, C, alpha_v, sigma)
+ * are PLACEHOLDERS and must be replaced with correct values computed
+ * offline using the ALP package (see ALP_1.98/).
+ *
+ * Gap combinations supported per matrix:
+ *   col 0: gap existence penalty
+ *   col 1: gap extension penalty
+ *   col 2: decline-to-align (INT2_MAX = not used)
+ *   col 3: Lambda  (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 4: K       (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 5: H       (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 6: alpha   (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 7: beta    (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 8: C       (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 9: alpha_v (PLACEHOLDER)
+ *   col 10: sigma  (PLACEHOLDER)
+ */
+
+/* RMBlast custom nucleotide substitution matrix KA parameters. -RMH-
+ * Values derived from ALP (Altschul-Lipman parameters) output.
+ * Column order: open, extend, INT2_MAX, lambda, K, H, alpha, beta, C, alpha_v, sigma
+ * where: alpha = ALP a_J + a_I, H = lambda/alpha,
+ *        beta = ALP b_J + b_I, alpha_v = ALP Alpha_J + Alpha_I, sigma = ALP Sigma */
